        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="center" font-weight="500" padding="0" font-size="22px">
            Austin Area CCL 2017/2018 Holiday Newsletter
          </mj-text>
          <mj-divider border-width="2px" border-color="#616161" width="45%" />
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify">
            <p>
              Happy new year, and welcome to the first edition of the Austin area CCL members’ newsletter, a new activity we're kicking off this year. Each month we will send a newsletter to local CCL members with the latest achievements and goals of CCL’s Austin area chapters.
            </p>
            <p>
              I am your newsletter compiler, Shalmali Joshi. I'm a volunteer in the West/Central chapter. If you have questions or suggestions, please <a href="mailto:shalmali.anu@gmail.com">email me</a>!
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify" font-weight="500" font-size="18px">
            3rd Coast Regional News
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text>
             The 5th Annual Regional Conference of the Texas, Louisiana, and Mississippi chapters of CCL will be held in Houston next month (February 3, 2018). Click <a href="https://donate.citizensclimateeducationcorp.org/houston/events/2018-third-coast-regional-conference/e158242">here</a> to register today with an early-bird discount and check out the agenda. A film screening and mixer is also scheduled for the evening before. Click <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/national-security-climate-risk-a-screening-panel-discussion-tickets-41909337958">here</a> to get tickets.
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>


      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify" font-weight="500" font-size="18px">
            Grasstops News
          </mj-text>
          <mj-image src="https://shalmalijoshi.github.io/cclnewsletter/ph1_cclnl1.png" />
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <p>
              Austin City Mayor Steve Adler and District 9 Council Member Kathie Tovo are our newest endorsers in November. Austin CCL Grasstops is planning a push for a City Council resolution endorsing the CCL's Carbon Fee and Dividend policy.
            </p>
            <p>
              In January, our grasstops coordinators Mike DeChellis and Mike Thompson are creating an endorser training program and a grasstops support group for CCL Austin. If you are interested in joining, contact them at <a href="mailto:michael.craig.thompson@gmail.com">michael.craig.thompson@gmail.com</a> or <a href="mailto:michael@dechellis.org">michael@dechellis.org</a>.
              </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-color="#E0E0E0" />
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify" font-weight="500" font-size="18px">
            Social Media Accomplishments
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <p>
              Mike Zangrilli has taken over the Austin area Facebook Page and is doing terrific work building our following. The CCL Austin Facebook page currently has 200 followers. We will continue to add followers by encouraging volunteers to engage their friends and continue the outreach process through other Austin Eco-friendly groups.
            </p>
            <p>
              Visit the overhauled <a href="https://www.facebook.com/CCLAustinTex/">Austin CCL Facebook</a> page to join, follow and share with your community!
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify" font-weight="500" font-size="18px">
            Lobbying Efforts
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <p>
              Multiple local volunteers travelled to Washington D.C. for Congressional Education Day in November. They had in-person meetings with Rep. John Carter's Legislative Director, Rep. Roger Williams’ legislative staff, and Rep. Lamar Smith’s office.
            </p>
         </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-color="#E0E0E0" />
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text align="justify" font-weight="500" font-size="18px">
            Media Outreach
          </mj-text>
          <mj-image width="250" src="https://shalmalijoshi.github.io/cclnewsletter/lte.png" />
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <p>
              In November, local members successfully published two letters to the editor with the Austin American-Statesman and four with the Williamson County Sun. The letters explored questions related to revenue neutral carbon pricing and distribution of net proceeds back to households.
            </p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
